author: BRIAN ROKOS
title: LAKE ELSINORE: Fall from motorcycle after 15-foot jump killed rider, coroner says
text:
By BRIAN ROKOS / STAFF WRITER
Published: Oct. 5, 2015 Updated: 1:36 p.m. LAKE ELSINORE: Fall from motorcycle after 15-foot jump killed rider, coroner says Print Photo Share Pin It More Galleries ADVERTISEMENT Related article Â» The man who died after being injured Friday at Lake Elsinore Motorsports Park crashed after going over a 15-foot jump on a motorcycle, the Riverside County Coroner's Office said Monday, Oct. 5.
Matthew Peters, 30, of Simi Valley, was injured about 11:40 a.m. Peters was pronounced dead at Inland Valley Regional Medical Center at 12:09 p.m. The circumstances surrounding Peters' death had not been available Friday.
Coroner's Sgt. Brent Sechrest said Monday that Peters was wearing a helmet but still was killed after he fell from his bike. He suffered blunt-force trauma, Sechrest said. Bystanders discovered him unresponsive.
A person who answered the phone at the motorsports park Monday said the facility was closed and that no one would be available to comment until Thursday.
